The Kirtland's Warbler is an endanger species of bird in the northern portion of the lower peninsula of Michigan and is found in nine different counties in the upper peninsula of Michigan. The kirtland's warbler can only nest under jack pine trees between 5 feet and 16 feet tall. Once the bottom branchs begin dying the bird must move onto another tree where the brances are low enough to protect the nest.  This bird is a Blue-gray and has a bright yellow breast.